12:55.992 --> 13:00.897
- Is that your friend in Pittsburgh?
- Yeah, if she is still my friend.

13:01.231 --> 13:05.469
That's nice.
I don't really have any girlfriends.

13:05.802 --> 13:08.805
My mom always felt, you know,
you can't trust women.

13:08.939 --> 13:10.907
I don't know about that.

13:11.241 --> 13:12.676
Oh, come on.

13:12.809 --> 13:16.947
Men know all about PMS. Somebody talked.

13:20.016 --> 13:22.385
<i>Your girl is lovely, Hubbell.</i>

13:22.519 --> 13:25.655
<i>Why don't you bring her for a drink
when you come?</i>

13:25.789 --> 13:26.890
<i>I can't.</i>

13:28.992 --> 13:30.894
<i>I know.</i>

13:41.505 --> 13:43.373
That-- That kills me.

13:43.507 --> 13:48.345
The way she, like,
brushes his hair off his forehead.

13:48.478 --> 13:51.615
Really gets me.

13:53.016 --> 13:55.285
So, well, which one of them were you?

13:55.418 --> 13:58.288
The one who loved too much
or the one who loved too little?

13:58.421 --> 13:59.990
Neither.

14:00.624 --> 14:02.859
I'm the one who spent three years
at happy hour...

14:02.993 --> 14:05.695
...and never went home with anybody
except the bartender.

14:05.829 --> 14:08.932
- Well, the bartender's somebody.
- Yeah.

14:09.065 --> 14:12.435
He was somebody, all right.

14:15.005 --> 14:16.873
I don't know.

14:17.474 --> 14:20.510
I don't know about men.

14:21.678 --> 14:23.780
I just don't get it.

14:23.914 --> 14:26.449
Maybe you're not into them.

14:26.583 --> 14:28.318
You mean...?

14:29.386 --> 14:32.722
- No.
- What do you mean, no?

14:32.856 --> 14:36.726
I think I scare them away
because I know what I want.

14:36.860 --> 14:40.597
Oh, well, tell me, what do you want?

14:41.631 --> 14:44.367
It's not very liberated, I know.

14:48.939 --> 14:52.375
I want a husband with a decent job.

14:52.976 --> 14:54.644
You know?

14:55.846 --> 14:59.683
And I want two kids, a boy and a girl...

14:59.816 --> 15:01.751
