- Hi.
- Hi.

01:10:30.744 --> 01:10:33.847
How are you?
Gonna teach me to play piano?

01:10:33.980 --> 01:10:38.151
- Is this gonna be good?
- That's fine. Don't scratch that, please.

01:10:47.294 --> 01:10:49.062
Hey, babe?

01:10:49.196 --> 01:10:50.997
Yeah?

01:10:53.700 --> 01:10:55.268
Marry me.

01:10:58.772 --> 01:11:02.042
- Get serious.
- I am serious.

01:11:02.175 --> 01:11:04.811
Get out of town.

01:11:06.980 --> 01:11:08.415
Look.

01:11:10.083 --> 01:11:12.919
- Freeze, sucker.
- I got you.

01:11:13.420 --> 01:11:15.922
I'll get you.

01:11:17.958 --> 01:11:20.026
- Stop, stop.
- Marry me.

01:11:20.160 --> 01:11:21.895
Marry me tomorrow.

01:11:23.930 --> 01:11:26.333
I can't marry you, Abe.

01:11:29.436 --> 01:11:32.339
You're not over him yet, are you?

01:11:34.407 --> 01:11:37.877
Well, we're all over him.

01:11:38.445 --> 01:11:41.881
Like, six feet over him.

01:12:09.342 --> 01:12:11.111
Mom?

01:12:11.244 --> 01:12:14.180
It was an accident. Or self-defense.

01:12:14.314 --> 01:12:18.518
I mean, I would never kill anybody on purpose,
or, like, in cold blood.

01:12:18.852 --> 01:12:21.321
Hey, did you ever see that movie?

01:12:28.228 --> 01:12:30.997
Let's get some rest, okay?

01:12:36.002 --> 01:12:39.272
You don't wanna marry me now, do you?

01:12:41.341 --> 01:12:45.245
We're together now. We're together.

01:12:46.546 --> 01:12:49.115
And that's not changing.

01:12:53.353 --> 01:12:55.422
She looks so thin.

01:12:57.424 --> 01:13:00.960
Look at you, honey.

01:13:01.394 --> 01:13:04.230
They gave us a terrible map at Hertz.

01:13:04.364 --> 01:13:07.901
I have been driving around
for an hour and a half.

01:13:08.034 --> 01:13:09.903
Is this your house?

01:13:10.036 --> 01:13:14.474
Isn't it quaint?
I need to use the little girls' room, darling.

01:13:14.607 --> 01:13:16.076
- Oh, sure, Mom.
- This heat.

01:13:16.209 --> 01:13:18.912
And the a.c. is NG, right, Jer?

01:13:19.045 --> 01:13:21.147
You know me. I like it so you need a sweater.

01:13:21.281 --> 01:13:23.149
It's two days. It'll be fine.

01:13:23.283 --> 01:13:25.485
- Hi, I'm Jerry.
- Oh, I'm sorry, Jerry. Robin.

01:13:25.618 --> 01:13:27.954
- My daughter, Robin.
- Pleased to meet you.

01:13:28.088 --> 01:13:30.256
I could've picked you up.
You didn't need a car.

01:13:30.390 --> 01:13:33.360
Well, you know me.
I'm so damned independent.

01:13:33.493 --> 01:13:36.229
Riding in other people's cars? Forget it.

01:13:36.363 --> 01:13:39.366
Well, isn't this nice?

01:13:39.499 --> 01:13:41.901
Oh, look, Jer, a cactus flower.

01:13:42.035 --> 01:13:44.237
They bloom once every hundred years.

01:13:44.371 --> 01:13:48.942
Quick, show me the potty, darling.
I'm about to burst.

01:13:49.075 --> 01:13:53.480
Anyway, Jane called me at work.
Wants to know how you are.

01:13:53.613 --> 01:13:55.548
- I'm fine.
- Who's Jane?

01:13:55.882 --> 01:13:58.251
Jane used to live here
up until a few days ago.

01:13:58.385 --> 01:14:00.387
Stay out of this. It's between me and Jane.

01:14:00.520 --> 01:14:04.057
Well, she asked for my advice,
so I told her she's antilesbian.

01:14:04.190 --> 01:14:06.126
- Am not.
- Who's a lesbian?

01:14:06.259 --> 01:14:08.061
Jane is.

01:14:08.194 --> 01:14:11.231
- And she was living here?
- Yes, ma'am.

01:14:11.364 --> 01:14:14.634
- I'm not antilesbian.
- Not you. Her.

01:14:14.968 --> 01:14:16.035
- Who?
- Jane.

01:14:16.169 --> 01:14:18.638
This is her old problem.
She creates this situation...

01:14:18.972 --> 01:14:22.008
...where she gets this rejection
that everyone sees coming.

01:14:22.142 --> 01:14:24.544
- She just wasn't being honest.
- It's a black thing too.

01:14:24.677 --> 01:14:27.680
- Jane is black?
- Yes, ma'am. She sure is.

01:14:28.014 --> 01:14:29.649
You can't live a lie. You just can't.

01:14:29.983 --> 01:14:33.153
Well, there's lying
and then there's just not telling.

01:14:33.286 --> 01:14:37.090
- Big diff.
- She's a black lesbian?

01:14:37.223 --> 01:14:41.594
- Yes, ma'am, that is right.
- And she was living here?

01:14:41.928 --> 01:14:44.964
- With you?
- No, no, no, she was just living here.

01:14:45.098 --> 01:14:47.267
They weren't, like, fucking or anything.

01:14:50.637 --> 01:14:52.972
- Were you?
- Were you?

01:14:53.106 --> 01:14:54.941
Were you?

01:14:57.477 --> 01:14:59.679
I'll get the coffee.

01:15:00.380 --> 01:15:02.949
I have to get going, babe.

01:15:03.082 --> 01:15:05.618
Why? Your shift doesn't start till 10:30.

01:15:05.952 --> 01:15:08.555
Don't you wanna go upstairs for a while?

01:15:08.688 --> 01:15:10.323
No, not tonight.

01:15:10.457 --> 01:15:13.059
- It was nice meeting you, ma'am.
- You going already?

01:15:13.193 --> 01:15:15.728
- We have dessert.
- Yes. Maybe next time. Thank you.

01:15:16.062 --> 01:15:19.032
- Well, good night.
- Good night.

01:15:20.967 --> 01:15:23.036
Maybe I'm just too fat now.

01:15:23.169 --> 01:15:26.539
Don't worry, dear. It's a natural thing.

01:15:28.208 --> 01:15:31.277
Will they live here after they get married?

01:15:31.411 --> 01:15:32.579
Who?

01:15:32.712 --> 01:15:36.516
Holly and, oh, that nice young man.
What is his name?

01:15:36.649 --> 01:15:38.351
Oh, Abe.

01:15:39.219 --> 01:15:41.588
Well, I'm not sure she wants to marry him.

01:15:42.489 --> 01:15:44.557
A pregnant girl?

01:15:44.691 --> 01:15:47.260
Is she crazy? She should grab him.

01:15:50.530 --> 01:15:52.532
Well, it's not really his baby.

01:15:52.665 --> 01:15:54.033
So what?

01:15:55.201 --> 01:15:58.004
She still should grab him.

01:15:59.372 --> 01:16:02.108
Believe me,
I know what she's gonna have to go through.

01:16:02.242 --> 01:16:05.144
You know, I'm a feminist too.

01:16:05.278 --> 01:16:07.480
I was a single mother after your father left.

01:16:08.481 --> 01:16:10.250
You think that was easy?

01:16:11.150 --> 01:16:14.053
I even voted for Carter twice.

01:16:14.754 --> 01:16:20.293
But you can't fight nature.
God knows you girls keep trying.

01:16:20.426 --> 01:16:22.495
Treating your men like side dishes...

01:16:22.629 --> 01:16:26.032
...you stick a fork in when needed,
just like men used to treat us.

01:16:26.165 --> 01:16:29.702
Mother, who am I treating?
Do you see a man here anywhere?

01:16:30.036 --> 01:16:32.705
No, I don't.

01:16:33.039 --> 01:16:35.508
And I think it's a problem.

01:16:36.342 --> 01:16:38.711
I don't understand
why you don't come home.

01:16:39.045 --> 01:16:40.280
I like it here, Mom.

01:16:40.413 --> 01:16:42.415
It's so strange.

01:16:42.549 --> 01:16:45.518
You're not exactly bubbling over
with happiness.

01:16:45.652 --> 01:16:48.421
It's a life, Mom, not a hayride.

01:16:48.555 --> 01:16:51.157
Honey, what is this?

01:16:51.291 --> 01:16:57.130
- Oh, my gosh. The police are here.
- Yes, I see the police, Mother.

01:17:00.833 --> 01:17:03.636
What the fuck is going on?
What the hell is going on?

01:17:03.770 --> 01:17:06.239
- Okay.
- Jane, what are you doing here?

01:17:06.372 --> 01:17:07.740
I called her.

01:17:08.074 --> 01:17:10.109
- I thought that she should know.
- Know what?

01:17:10.710 --> 01:17:13.580
- He's arresting me.
- What for?

01:17:13.713 --> 01:17:16.683
You know what for, Robin. Pittsburgh.

01:17:16.816 --> 01:17:19.118
- You told him?
- Yes, she told me.

01:17:19.252 --> 01:17:21.254
I take this name seriously.

01:17:21.387 --> 01:17:23.656
I cannot tell a lie.

01:17:23.790 --> 01:17:25.858
That was Washington, schmuck.

01:17:27.327 --> 01:17:28.528
Whatever.

01:17:28.661 --> 01:17:32.298
Anyway, I'm going to stand by Holly
100 percent.

01:17:32.432 --> 01:17:34.334
But I am sworn to uphold the law.

01:17:34.467 --> 01:17:37.670
And I don't believe I would be any use to her
if I broke my oath.

01:17:37.804 --> 01:17:39.639
Now, would I?

01:17:40.773 --> 01:17:42.442
He really loves me.

01:17:42.575 --> 01:17:45.311
Oh, yeah,
I can tell by the manacles on your wrists.

01:17:45.445 --> 01:17:47.413
Right this way, miss.

01:17:49.282 --> 01:17:52.785
Don't say a word, not to him, not to anybody.
We'll get you a lawyer.

01:17:54.520 --> 01:17:55.622
I'll miss you guys.

01:18:14.807 --> 01:18:18.177
Now, I promise you
that they are going to treat her right.

01:18:19.245 --> 01:18:22.482
They know that she is going to be
my future wife.

01:18:27.553 --> 01:18:29.255
Son of a bitch.

01:18:30.623 --> 01:18:34.460
Honey, what in the world is going on?

01:18:35.261 --> 01:18:38.665
<i>I feel like I've just seen
America's Most Wanted in person.</i>

01:18:38.798 --> 01:18:42.335
- This has got to be the mother.
- Jane, please.

01:18:42.468 --> 01:18:45.938
- Yes, I am. And who are you?
- I'm the lesbo.

01:18:46.272 --> 01:18:48.641
I used to live here
till your daughter threw me out.

01:18:48.775 --> 01:18:49.909
- Well, I'm sorry.
- Mother.

01:18:50.243 --> 01:18:53.446
Yeah, me too.
But I think this makes her real happy...

01:18:53.579 --> 01:18:56.282
...because now she's got the house
all to herself.

01:18:56.416 --> 01:18:58.651
Cut it out. You're just being mean.

01:18:58.785 --> 01:19:00.186
Jane. Stop.

01:19:01.354 --> 01:19:04.857
- You know, she's gonna need our help.
- No, not our help.

01:19:05.191 --> 01:19:06.592
I'll take care of this myself.

01:19:06.726 --> 01:19:08.361
- Okay.
- Okay.

01:19:08.494 --> 01:19:11.597
Fine, fine, fine.

01:19:12.799 --> 01:19:15.268
- They do that now, don't they?
- What?

01:19:15.401 --> 01:19:18.271
- Call themselves lesbos.
- Oh, Mom.

01:19:18.404 --> 01:19:20.940
And she makes it sound like a compliment.

01:19:22.775 --> 01:19:24.243
She wants to confess.

01:19:24.377 --> 01:19:27.447
She says she doesn't wanna bring her child
into a world of lies.

01:19:27.580 --> 01:19:29.716
You have nothing to worry about, Henry.

01:19:29.849 --> 01:19:32.552
Holly promised me
she is going to keep her mouth shut...

01:19:32.685 --> 01:19:34.854
...as long as she does not have to lie
out loud.

01:19:34.987 --> 01:19:37.890
We wouldn't be here if it wasn't for you,
you brownnosing putz.

01:19:38.224 --> 01:19:40.760
- I took an oath, Jane.
- Yeah, you took a fucking oath.

01:19:40.893 --> 01:19:44.263
Now we're stuck in Pittsburgh,
Holly's on trial because of your oath.

01:19:44.397 --> 01:19:46.466
- So, what exactly do they have?
- Nothing.

01:19:46.599 --> 01:19:49.302
Except for Abe's testimony,
and that's just hearsay.

01:19:49.435 --> 01:19:50.570
That is the truth.

01:19:50.703 --> 01:19:55.374
Oh, shut up. Nobody wants to hear the truth.
But aside from that, what do they have?

01:19:55.508 --> 01:19:57.643
They have the Polaroid.

01:19:59.645 --> 01:20:01.948
- The Polaroid?
- Yes.

01:20:02.281 --> 01:20:04.684
I mentioned that I had seen a snapshot.

01:20:04.817 --> 01:20:08.721
It's on the list of exhibits. But come on.
What the hell can they do with that?

01:20:09.355 --> 01:20:11.023
Cold-blooded?

01:20:11.357 --> 01:20:12.959
Cruel?

01:20:13.760 --> 01:20:15.595
Inhuman?

01:20:15.928 --> 01:20:18.931
What words would you use to describe
the woman who posed...

01:20:19.265 --> 01:20:20.566
...and took this photograph?

01:20:20.700 --> 01:20:22.735
This is a photograph...

01:20:22.869 --> 01:20:25.905
...of a man who in a few short hours
will be dead...

01:20:26.038 --> 01:20:30.042
...from wounds inflicted by this woman
that you see before you.

01:20:30.376 --> 01:20:34.647
And not surprisingly, everything that you say
tends to exonerate your friend.

01:20:35.381 --> 01:20:38.818
- Sorry. It's the truth.
- Not coincidentally, it tends to exonerate you.

01:20:38.951 --> 01:20:41.521
- There are no charges against me.
- Yet.

01:20:41.654 --> 01:20:43.556
Oh, come on. Your Honor.

01:20:43.689 --> 01:20:46.559
Is he allowed to just intimidate me like this?

01:20:46.692 --> 01:20:48.561
Mr. Massarelli, please.

01:20:48.694 --> 01:20:50.930
I apologize, Your Honor.
It was unintentional.

01:20:51.063 --> 01:20:55.368
What is the nature of your friendship
with Holly Pulchik?

01:20:55.501 --> 01:20:58.971
- Excuse me?
- I'm sorry. Let me rephrase the question.

01:20:59.305 --> 01:21:03.910
- How would you characterize your friendship?
- I would call her my friend.

01:21:06.979 --> 01:21:10.817
- Come on. What is this "friendship" stuff?
- That's what I'm trying to find out.

01:21:10.950 --> 01:21:13.686
Let me put this delicately
to avoid offending the court.

01:21:13.820 --> 01:21:17.490
Is there a romantic character
to your friendship?

01:21:17.623 --> 01:21:18.958
- Objection.
- Overruled.

01:21:19.091 --> 01:21:21.828
- You may proceed, Mr. Massarelli.
- Thank you.

01:21:21.961 --> 01:21:23.996
To repeat, Ms. Deluca...

01:21:24.330 --> 01:21:27.667
...is there a romantic character
to your friendship with the defendant?

01:21:27.800 --> 01:21:30.536
- No, Mr. Maserati, there is not.
- Massarelli.

01:21:30.670 --> 01:21:32.538
Oh, sorry. Unintentional.

01:21:32.672 --> 01:21:36.042
You are one of these gay women we read about.
Or do you prefer "lesbians"?

01:21:36.375 --> 01:21:38.010
- Do I prefer them to you?
- Are you gay?

01:21:38.344 --> 01:21:39.545
- Do I look gay?
- Your Honor.

01:21:39.679 --> 01:21:43.583
- Please answer the question.
- Are you gay?

01:21:44.383 --> 01:21:45.885
Yes, I am.

01:21:46.018 --> 01:21:48.888
And I'm sure you hear that from women
all the time.

01:21:49.021 --> 01:21:51.891
But in my case, it happens to be true.

01:21:52.525 --> 01:21:56.629
She's scared shitless,
just like I would be after today.

01:21:56.762 --> 01:21:58.998
No, I don't want you to do that, Anna.

01:21:59.131 --> 01:22:04.637
Okay? I don't want you to do that.
I'll call you tonight. All right? Bye.

01:22:06.772 --> 01:22:08.708
Schmuck.

01:22:09.108 --> 01:22:10.142
You did your best.

01:22:10.476 --> 01:22:13.045
Yeah, I did.
Which is more than I can say for you.

01:22:13.379 --> 01:22:15.781
Justice is hard.

01:22:15.915 --> 01:22:17.717
Justice?

01:22:17.850 --> 01:22:19.652
You call this justice?

01:22:19.785 --> 01:22:22.588
This girl protects herself
against some marauding asshole...

01:22:22.722 --> 01:22:25.491
...who uses her as a punching bag,
and she's going to jail.

01:22:25.625 --> 01:22:28.160
You call that justice? Is that what you want?

01:22:28.494 --> 01:22:30.930
I want Holly to be my wife.

01:22:31.797 --> 01:22:35.635
- I want us to be a family.
- Where? In the joint?

01:22:36.702 --> 01:22:38.905
I don't know that.

01:22:39.038 --> 01:22:41.908
But I do know that there's no kind of family
without the law.

01:22:42.041 --> 01:22:43.542
None whatsoever.

01:22:43.676 --> 01:22:48.714
Because the law that governs the society
is the same law that holds the family together.

01:22:48.848 --> 01:22:52.018
Where'd you read that?
On the side of a Cheerios box?

01:22:57.156 --> 01:22:59.859
You think I love her less now.

01:23:02.194 --> 01:23:03.963
But I don't.

01:23:07.733 --> 01:23:09.769
I love her more.

01:23:10.469 --> 01:23:13.105
That is why I had to do this.

01:23:18.110 --> 01:23:20.146
Come on.

01:23:21.047 --> 01:23:23.215
Come on, come on.

01:23:34.860 --> 01:23:38.064
- And they lived happily ever after.
- Did I wake you?

01:23:38.197 --> 01:23:42.234
No. I was just looking for a drink.

01:23:43.502 --> 01:23:46.038
- There's beer.
- No.

01:23:46.172 --> 01:23:50.876
I had some bourbon from the plane,
but I seem to have finished it.

01:23:51.944 --> 01:23:53.112
What are you doing?

01:23:55.247 --> 01:23:59.952
I thought somehow if I made this trip again,
we'd all be here at the end like this.

01:24:00.086 --> 01:24:04.790
Oh, honey.
Nobody was happy in these pictures.

01:24:04.924 --> 01:24:06.993
Except maybe you.

01:24:07.727 --> 01:24:10.663
Tommy was already so frail.

01:24:10.796 --> 01:24:12.131
And your father....

01:24:13.566 --> 01:24:15.134
Well, you loved him, didn't you?

01:24:16.802 --> 01:24:17.970
Yes, I did.

01:24:19.071 --> 01:24:21.173
With all my heart.

01:24:21.707 --> 01:24:23.275
But I lost him.

01:24:23.609 --> 01:24:25.611
And Tommy too. And that's that.

01:24:25.745 --> 01:24:29.582
You just have to let it go, Robin.
Just let it go.

01:24:29.715 --> 01:24:33.819
- I can't.
- You have to, darling.

01:24:33.953 --> 01:24:37.056
Because it's never gonna come out
any differently.

01:24:37.189 --> 01:24:39.892
No matter how many times
you make this trip.

01:24:40.026 --> 01:24:41.761
I know that.

01:24:43.829 --> 01:24:46.265
When we lost Tommy...

01:24:47.767 --> 01:24:51.103
...well, your father just couldn't live with that.

01:24:53.105 --> 01:24:55.307
I don't blame him.

01:24:56.675 --> 01:24:59.612
It's not right, losing your children.

01:25:01.113 --> 01:25:04.150
Children are supposed to live after you.

01:25:04.917 --> 01:25:06.952
Oh, honey.

01:25:07.319 --> 01:25:10.656
Are you crying? Oh, my gosh.

01:25:11.590 --> 01:25:14.660
Do you know
I don't ever remember you crying?

01:25:15.728 --> 01:25:18.197
Even when you were a baby.

01:25:19.165 --> 01:25:20.566
Isn't that funny?

01:25:26.138 --> 01:25:28.007
I'm sorry.

01:25:32.078 --> 01:25:34.880
I know you're not well, darling.

01:25:36.015 --> 01:25:39.785
I don't know what it is,
and I don't wanna know.

01:25:40.119 --> 01:25:41.787
But I know you'll get better.

01:25:42.221 --> 01:25:44.890
You were always the strong one.

01:25:45.024 --> 01:25:47.359
I can't lose you.

01:25:48.227 --> 01:25:50.796
I can't just lose everybody.

01:25:52.665 --> 01:25:55.267
I do the best I can.

01:25:55.835 --> 01:25:58.204
I know it's not enough.

01:25:58.337 --> 01:25:59.738
And I'm sorry.

01:26:00.239 --> 01:26:03.375
But that's what you get in life, you know?

01:26:03.709 --> 01:26:06.011
You get whoever you end up with.

01:26:06.145 --> 01:26:09.748
Whoever is willing to stick by you
and fight for you...

01:26:09.882 --> 01:26:12.351
...when everyone else is gone.

01:26:12.885 --> 01:26:19.058
And it ain't always who you expect,
but you just have to make do.

01:26:20.326 --> 01:26:22.161
I'm not complaining, Mom.

01:26:23.162 --> 01:26:26.699
"Never complain. Never explain."

01:26:26.832 --> 01:26:28.667
Katharine Hepburn.

01:26:28.801 --> 01:26:32.037
<i>She said that in Redbook last month.</i>

01:26:32.171 --> 01:26:34.807
It's a good motto, isn't it?

01:26:36.642 --> 01:26:39.278
Best I can do is pretend
like you never testified.

01:26:39.411 --> 01:26:42.748
- Just go on like it never happened.
- Go on to what?

01:26:42.882 --> 01:26:46.085
Honestly, I don't know.

01:26:56.862 --> 01:26:59.131
All right, this is the situation.

01:26:59.265 --> 01:27:02.768
I am still angry,
I do not forgive you for anything...

01:27:02.902 --> 01:27:04.970
...and I don't wanna talk about it.

01:27:05.104 --> 01:27:06.138
Anna filled me in.

01:27:06.272 --> 01:27:09.775
She told me everything I needed to know
about the trial so far.

01:27:09.909 --> 01:27:11.410
And I know I can help.

01:27:11.744 --> 01:27:15.080
Because even if I can't,
I couldn't make it any worse.

01:27:15.214 --> 01:27:18.684
And Holly is as much my responsibility
as anyone else's...

01:27:18.817 --> 01:27:22.788
...and so are you,
because you are my family and I love you.

01:27:25.391 --> 01:27:28.894
Now, I feel fine.

01:27:29.028 --> 01:27:33.699
My T cells are over a hundred,
and I'm raring to go.

01:27:33.832 --> 01:27:36.235
So unless you wanna waste time
being stubborn...

01:27:36.368 --> 01:27:40.139
...I suggest we get me on the stand
as soon as possible.

01:28:00.759 --> 01:28:03.762
You expect us to believe
that the defendant...

01:28:03.896 --> 01:28:07.199
...pregnant with this man's child,
would leave him and never look back?

01:28:07.333 --> 01:28:12.071
It was over. He beat her and abused her.
I saw. I saw how he treated her.

01:28:12.204 --> 01:28:15.374
But not to call. Not to leave an address
so he could forward her mail.

01:28:15.507 --> 01:28:17.009
And practical reasons aside...

01:28:17.142 --> 01:28:20.446
...let's say she did strike a blow for self-defense.
Let's just assume.

01:28:20.779 --> 01:28:25.084
And she decides to let him stew
in his own juices for a while.

01:28:25.217 --> 01:28:27.886
But a couple of hours, a few days later,
she realizes:

01:28:28.020 --> 01:28:33.092
"He's my little baby's daddy.
And you know what? He's not so bad.

01:28:33.225 --> 01:28:36.362
Maybe he's got a temper."
But all she knows is she needs him.

01:28:36.495 --> 01:28:41.000
- She needs to call him.
- But it was over between them.

01:28:42.801 --> 01:28:46.338
I know you think a girl like her,
the most important thing in her life is a man.

01:28:46.472 --> 01:28:49.275
But she didn't need him. She had us.

01:28:49.408 --> 01:28:52.011
I hardly think
that you're a replacement for a father.

01:28:52.144 --> 01:28:53.946
I don't know what it is...

01:28:55.214 --> 01:28:58.450
...but there's something that goes on
between women.

01:28:59.518 --> 01:29:03.789
You men know that
because it's the same for you.

01:29:03.922 --> 01:29:07.059
I'm not saying one sex is better
than the other.

01:29:07.192 --> 01:29:10.229
I'm just saying...

01:29:10.963 --> 01:29:12.331
...like speaks to like.

01:29:13.832 --> 01:29:17.336
Love or whatever doesn't always keep...

01:29:17.469 --> 01:29:20.906
...so you find out what does, if you're lucky.

01:29:23.942 --> 01:29:28.280
Well, thank you for that illuminating view
of the war between the sexes.

01:29:28.414 --> 01:29:32.484
- Are you a lesbian too, Ms. Nickerson?
- No, sir.

01:29:32.818 --> 01:29:34.987
But at times I understand the inclination.

01:29:36.522 --> 01:29:38.524
Suppose there is this bond between women.

01:29:38.857 --> 01:29:40.993
- Suppose men are disposable.
- I didn't say that.

01:29:41.126 --> 01:29:43.195
If that's the case,
why should we believe you?

01:29:43.328 --> 01:29:46.932
Wouldn't you say anything,
wouldn't you do anything, to keep your sister...

01:29:47.066 --> 01:29:49.401
...keep your bosom buddy,
so to speak, out of jail?

01:29:49.535 --> 01:29:53.472
- I'm under oath. I wouldn't perjure myself.
- I'm glad I don't have to remind you.

01:29:53.605 --> 01:29:56.975
And just for the record...

01:29:58.043 --> 01:30:02.181
...you didn't know until the police told you...

01:30:02.314 --> 01:30:04.316
...that this man was dead of his wounds?

01:30:05.150 --> 01:30:10.556
If I'm lying, may I be struck down
with some terrible disease.

01:30:11.590 --> 01:30:15.461
Okay. All right, good news.

01:30:15.594 --> 01:30:17.262
Got an offer.

01:30:17.396 --> 01:30:20.365
Involuntary manslaughter,
extenuating circumstances.

01:30:20.499 --> 01:30:23.936
One to two years. Parole after six months.

01:30:24.069 --> 01:30:29.374
I got you minimum security in Arizona,
two hours from home and good medical care.

01:30:30.442 --> 01:30:33.345
I'd hate to have my baby in jail.

01:30:33.479 --> 01:30:36.181
What are the chances for an acquittal?

01:30:36.315 --> 01:30:40.452
He's dead as a result of her actions.
And juries wanna make someone pay for that.

01:30:40.586 --> 01:30:45.224
She didn't testify in her own defense,
and I don't know how much good you did her.

01:30:45.357 --> 01:30:50.629
I mean, my baby will have a mother
who's a convicted felon.

01:30:50.963 --> 01:30:53.365
I don't know. What do you think?

01:30:53.499 --> 01:30:56.068
- Under the circumstances....
- I'd have her....

01:30:56.201 --> 01:31:00.906
I mean Abe.
What do you think about that, babe?

01:31:02.141 --> 01:31:04.643
I think that you should take it.

01:31:04.977 --> 01:31:07.379
And I will keep the baby until you get out.

01:31:07.513 --> 01:31:10.115
- Yeah, but--
- That's what I'll do, then.

01:31:10.249 --> 01:31:13.552
Fine. I'll tell them we'll take it.

01:31:19.491 --> 01:31:21.160
I love you.

01:31:21.293 --> 01:31:23.629
- I gotta get in there with you.
- Do you?

01:31:23.962 --> 01:31:26.331
I want you so much, babe.

01:31:27.699 --> 01:31:29.601
Could we have a minute?

01:31:30.302 --> 01:31:33.472
- Yes.
- Yeah. We'll see you later.

01:31:36.074 --> 01:31:37.676
Get in here.

01:31:47.152 --> 01:31:50.322
Babe, I missed you so much.

01:31:51.490 --> 01:31:54.660
Well, so much for the bonds
between women.

01:31:54.993 --> 01:31:58.130
- I love you.
- You can't fight that.

01:31:58.263 --> 01:32:00.966
I love you so much.

01:32:01.099 --> 01:32:04.203
- Your baby's gonna be fine.
- You were pretty good in there.

01:32:04.336 --> 01:32:08.740
Whatever happened to
"Honesty's the best policy"?

01:32:09.074 --> 01:32:11.443
You don't wanna go overboard.

01:32:19.384 --> 01:32:21.687
You know,
I been thinking and thinking about this...

01:32:22.020 --> 01:32:24.089
...so I wanna say it.

01:32:25.224 --> 01:32:29.628
I am really, really sorry. I truly am.

01:32:29.761 --> 01:32:33.532
Yeah, me too. I get so angry so fast.

01:32:35.200 --> 01:32:37.135
It's just....

01:32:40.205 --> 01:32:42.174
It's lonely.

01:32:43.642 --> 01:32:48.313
Between me and everybody else,
there's all this space all the time.

01:32:48.447 --> 01:32:51.550
And it gets bigger and bigger...

01:32:52.784 --> 01:32:55.320
...and I'm on one side...

01:32:56.154 --> 01:33:01.660
...and I'm screaming, and they're waving.

01:33:03.262 --> 01:33:09.768
And the one person I think I'm holding
is waving too.

01:33:14.072 --> 01:33:16.241
I'm holding you.

01:33:21.413 --> 01:33:25.484
There won't be any more lies between us.

01:33:25.617 --> 01:33:28.520
Not even for my own good.

01:33:29.621 --> 01:33:32.357
- No, ma'am.
- Good.

01:33:33.125 --> 01:33:35.494
- I'm gonna go call Anna. She's--
- Jane.

01:33:35.627 --> 01:33:39.431
Yeah? Yeah? What's the matter?

01:33:39.564 --> 01:33:41.667
What's the matter? Hey. Hey.

01:33:41.800 --> 01:33:44.236
Abe. Abe!

01:33:49.741 --> 01:33:52.277
<i>Elaine. Jane.</i>

01:33:52.411 --> 01:33:56.548
<i>Listen, I'm sorry to wake you,
but we're back in Tucson...</i>

01:33:56.682 --> 01:33:59.351
<i>...and she's in the hospital.</i>

01:35:17.195 --> 01:35:19.564
What curse, honey? Who?

01:35:19.698 --> 01:35:21.867
The one on my friend.

01:35:22.200 --> 01:35:26.238
Remember when I came to see you,
you said there was a curse on a friend of mine?

01:35:27.205 --> 01:35:29.775
It's my friend Robin. She's....

01:35:29.908 --> 01:35:32.944
Look, you know, I don't believe in this stuff.
You know that.

01:35:33.278 --> 01:35:35.313
I thought it couldn't hurt to come see you.

01:35:35.447 --> 01:35:38.683
Oh, Robin. That's the girl with AIDS.

01:35:38.817 --> 01:35:42.921
- Anna's friend.
- She's my friend.

01:35:45.424 --> 01:35:47.426
I see.

01:35:55.867 --> 01:35:58.670
- So can you do it?
- Do what?

01:35:59.371 --> 01:36:01.440
Take the curse off of her.
You said you could.

01:36:02.741 --> 01:36:05.210
It's AIDS, honey.

01:36:05.844 --> 01:36:10.315
I know that, but right now
it's just a lung infection, see?

01:36:11.249 --> 01:36:13.285
I don't want a miracle.

01:36:13.418 --> 01:36:16.321
I just wanna give her a 51-49 shot.

01:36:16.455 --> 01:36:20.325
I mean, look, I brought money.
I could pay you right now.

01:36:22.861 --> 01:36:24.996
Pay when it works.

01:36:25.330 --> 01:36:27.933
I can't promise anything.

01:36:34.573 --> 01:36:36.741
Don't wake her up.

01:36:36.875 --> 01:36:39.311
Just doing my job.

01:36:41.446 --> 01:36:43.515
Is that a cold?

01:36:43.648 --> 01:36:46.585
Because she can't afford an infection.
I'll have to mask you.

01:36:46.718 --> 01:36:47.719
Are you blind?

01:36:47.853 --> 01:36:50.388
Can't you see she's been crying?
It's her mother.

01:36:50.522 --> 01:36:53.925
People think they're being nice,
but they come in with colds, and it's not--

01:36:54.259 --> 01:36:56.294
It's not a goddamn cold.

01:36:56.428 --> 01:36:59.264
- Don't be such a hoo-hoo.
- And what's a hoo-hoo?

01:36:59.397 --> 01:37:01.600
It's a cunt, dear.

01:37:01.733 --> 01:37:03.902
Now, why don't you leave us alone?

01:37:25.924 --> 01:37:27.359
Tommy?

01:37:37.502 --> 01:37:38.770
Hey.

01:37:38.904 --> 01:37:41.072
It's just me.

01:37:46.912 --> 01:37:50.382
- I know.
- Okay.

01:37:51.516 --> 01:37:53.451
Where's Mom?

01:37:54.419 --> 01:37:56.955
She had to go back to the house.

01:37:57.989 --> 01:38:00.091
Will you call her?

01:38:01.326 --> 01:38:02.460
Sure.

01:38:12.470 --> 01:38:17.642
Yeah, hi. She's asking for you.

01:38:19.411 --> 01:38:20.979
Bye.

01:38:24.950 --> 01:38:27.652
Do you want me to get a doctor?

01:38:31.756 --> 01:38:33.491
No.

01:38:44.603 --> 01:38:48.006
I had a crush on a woman once.

01:38:49.507 --> 01:38:51.610
I was 10.

01:38:52.110 --> 01:38:55.146
That's when I had crushes on boys.

01:38:57.649 --> 01:39:00.785
She was a strawberry blond.

01:39:02.921 --> 01:39:05.457
That's what my mom called her.

01:39:06.658 --> 01:39:11.930
She was the babysitter
at a hotel we stayed at...

01:39:12.063 --> 01:39:15.734
...right before my dad went to Vietnam.

01:39:15.867 --> 01:39:18.670
She was beautiful.

01:39:18.803 --> 01:39:21.406
Strawberry blond.

01:39:22.173 --> 01:39:25.443
I used to be a strawberry blond too.

01:39:31.750 --> 01:39:35.520
It was me you loved, wasn't it?

01:39:38.123 --> 01:39:39.724
Yeah.

01:39:42.794 --> 01:39:44.796
Still.

01:39:47.499 --> 01:39:49.834
Well, I loved you too.

01:39:57.709 --> 01:40:03.048
I don't want a funeral, but Mom will.

01:40:03.181 --> 01:40:05.784
But it's gotta be here.

01:40:05.917 --> 01:40:09.054
Don't let her take me back to San Diego.

01:40:15.060 --> 01:40:20.765
And afterwards you could have a big party
at the house, okay?

01:40:26.571 --> 01:40:28.807
Big party.

01:40:44.522 --> 01:40:46.191
Big party.

01:41:05.877 --> 01:41:08.847
Push, Holly. You can do it.
Push right into it.

01:41:10.582 --> 01:41:12.217
Come on, push, Holly. You can do it.

01:41:12.550 --> 01:41:15.720
- Nice deep breath and push.
- Pulling it down.

01:41:15.854 --> 01:41:19.591
- Perfect, perfect. Come on. You can do it.
- Give us a real good push now.

01:41:19.724 --> 01:41:22.827
- You're almost done.
- The baby's coming.

01:42:12.644 --> 01:42:15.847
I wanted to be here for her, you know,
to help her with the breathing.

01:42:15.980 --> 01:42:18.349
Next time.
You ever seen one of these things?

01:42:18.683 --> 01:42:19.717
They're really ugly.

01:42:19.851 --> 01:42:21.786
- Where are they?
- Let's go.

01:42:21.920 --> 01:42:23.988
Wait. Whoa, wait a minute. Come on, man.

01:42:30.929 --> 01:42:32.931
{\An8}"Fristad."

01:42:33.064 --> 01:42:35.133
"Mitchell."

01:42:35.834 --> 01:42:36.968
{\An8}"Pulchik."

01:42:47.078 --> 01:42:49.147
Don't look at me.

01:42:55.720 --> 01:42:59.224
- I can't wait to see the baby.
- All right!

01:43:00.625 --> 01:43:04.362
- Welcome back.
- We made it. We're back home.

01:43:04.696 --> 01:43:06.631
- Hi.
- Coming through.

01:43:06.764 --> 01:43:11.069
- You look beautiful.
- My baby's baby.

01:43:11.803 --> 01:43:15.240
- You look great.
- Thank you.

01:43:16.107 --> 01:43:18.276
Isn't she beautiful?

01:43:18.409 --> 01:43:21.412
Hi, little one. Come here.

01:43:21.746 --> 01:43:23.014
Welcome.

01:43:23.147 --> 01:43:25.650
Welcome, Mary Todd.

01:44:38.723 --> 01:44:41.859
Push it right out of there. Push it out.

01:45:03.448 --> 01:45:07.418
It was rough going there.
But she managed to pull herself through.

01:45:07.752 --> 01:45:11.322
And the next day
the pentamidine kicked in, so....

01:45:11.923 --> 01:45:14.292
What are her T cells now?

01:45:14.425 --> 01:45:19.897
They're about 35. They were under 20 before.

01:45:20.031 --> 01:45:23.334
She doesn't look good.

01:45:24.769 --> 01:45:28.940
She looks great, okay?

01:45:30.308 --> 01:45:34.112
We wanna welcome Holly home
with her new baby and her new husband, Abe.

01:45:35.313 --> 01:45:37.015
Great to have you back.

01:45:39.417 --> 01:45:42.387
We're all glad to be here with our friends.

01:45:42.520 --> 01:45:45.556
And I want you right now,
ladies and gentlemen...

01:45:45.890 --> 01:45:49.827
...to put your hands together
and give a round of warm applause...

01:45:49.961 --> 01:45:54.899
<i>...to 1983's fourth runner-up
in the Star Search Talent Competition.</i>

01:45:55.033 --> 01:45:58.403
No, no, no, Jane.
It was third runner-up, not fourth.

01:45:58.536 --> 01:45:59.537
I told her.

01:45:59.871 --> 01:46:03.808
